17/01/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis, who leads the ruling New Democracy Party, met with George Papandreou, leader of the main opposition PASOK party, on Monday (16 January). They agreed on the need for dialogue and consensus regarding constitutional reforms. It was the first of a series of talks about amendments aimed, in part, at ensuring better monitoring of election spending and curbing misappropriation by political parties. (ANA, MPA - 16/01/06 
